<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,261,683]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,334,360]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Remarks.</emphasis>
A single anomphalous bellerophontiform shell and a fragment show strengthened, thread-like growth lines and a distinct selenizone with slightly straight short lunulae, which are the general characteristics of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Montfort" authorityYear="1808" box="[151,288,405,431]" class="Gastropoda" family="Bellerophontidae" genus="Bellerophon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bellerophontida" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,288,405,431]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Bellerophon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The involute shell is slightly elongated and inflated and the whorl profile is moderately well rounded. The present specimens resemble 
<taxonomicName authority="de Koninck, 1863" authorityName="de Koninck" authorityYear="1863" box="[521,994,441,467]" class="Gastropoda" family="Bellerophontidae" genus="Bellerophon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bellerophontida" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="jonesianus">
<emphasis box="[521,785,441,467]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Bellerophon jonesianus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Koninck, L. G. de" box="[792,994,441,467]" firstAuthor="de Koninck" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" refId="ref25516" refString="Koninck, L. G. de (1863) Meimoire sur les Fossiles Paleiozoiques Recueillis dans l'Inde par M. le Docteur Fleming. H. Dessaain, LieIge, 44 pp." type="book" year="1863">de Koninck, 1863</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. The specimens assigned as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Koninck" authorityYear="1863" class="Gastropoda" family="Bellerophontidae" genus="Bellerophon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bellerophontida" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="jonesianus">
<emphasis box="[1312,1329,442,467]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">B</emphasis>
. cf. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">jonesianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Mansuy" box="[267,444,477,504]" firstAuthor="Mansuy" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="1 - 133" refId="ref26022" refString="Mansuy, H. (1913 a) Faunes des calcaires a Productus de l'Indochine. Memoires du Service Geologique de l'Indochine, 2 (4), 1 - 133." type="journal article" year="1913" yearSuffix="a">
Mansuy (1913 
<emphasis box="[430,444,478,503]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">a</emphasis>
</bibRefCitation>
, p. 103, pl. 11, figs 1–2) from the Permian of 
<collectingCountry box="[970,1024,478,504]" name="Laos" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Laos</collectingCountry>
is the most similar form. The specimens assigned to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Koninck" authorityYear="1863" box="[353,505,514,540]" class="Gastropoda" family="Bellerophontidae" genus="Bellerophon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bellerophontida" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="jonesianus">
<emphasis box="[353,370,514,539]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[385,505,514,539]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">jonesianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Delpey" box="[549,706,513,539]" firstAuthor="Delpey" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="345 - 369" refId="ref23861" refString="Delpey, G. (1941) Les Gasteropodes permiens du Cambodge. Journal de Conchyologie, 84, 255 - 278, 345 - 369." type="journal article" year="1941">Delpey (1941</bibRefCitation>
, p. 346, figs 21–22) from the Permian of 
<collectingCountry box="[1181,1299,513,539]" name="Cambodia" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Cambodia</collectingCountry>
, by 
<bibRefCitation author="Waagen" firstAuthor="Waagen" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="1 - 183" refId="ref28294" refString="Waagen, W. (1880) Salt-Range Fossils. I. Productus Limestone fossils. 2. Pisces-Cephalopoda: supplement Gasteropoda. Memoirs of the Geological Survey of India (Palaeontologia Indica), 13, 1 - 183." type="journal article" year="1880">Waagen (1880</bibRefCitation>
, p. 135, pl. 8, figs 1–2) from the Permian of 
<collectingCountry box="[726,821,549,575]" name="Pakistan" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
and by Nützel &amp; 
<bibRefCitation author="Nakazawa" box="[1023,1216,549,575]" firstAuthor="Nakazawa" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="103 - 169" refId="ref27024" refString="Nu ¨ tzel, A. &amp; Nakazawa, K. (2012) Permian (Capitanian) gastropods from the Akasaka Limestone (Gifu Prefecture, Japan). Journal of Systematic Palaeontology, 10, 103 - 169. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 14772019.2010.549659" type="journal article" year="2012">Nakazawa (2012</bibRefCitation>
, p. 109, fig. 8A–H) from the Permian of 
<collectingCountry box="[390,454,586,612]" name="Japan" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Japan</collectingCountry>
also resemble the present specimens. The present specimens resemble 
<taxonomicName authority="Ketwetsuriya &amp; Karapunar &amp; Charoentitirat &amp; Nützel, 2020" authorityName="Ketwetsuriya &amp; Karapunar &amp; Charoentitirat &amp; Nützel" authorityYear="2020" box="[1264,1436,586,612]" class="Gastropoda" family="Bellerophontidae" genus="Bellerophon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bellerophontida" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="erawanensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1264,1281,586,611]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1296,1436,586,611]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">erawanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[151,239,622,648]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
they have a more elongated shape, more distinct selenizone, stronger growth lines and wider interspaces between the thread-like growth lines.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
